  "body": "I heard that `setState` method is async\r\n\r\nBut I'm confused in my demo, they have the same log in console\r\n \r\nDoes anyone know why?\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\ncomponentDidMount() {\r\n    setTimeout(() => {\r\n        for (let i = 0; i < 5; i++) {\r\n            console.log(this.state.num);\r\n            this.setState({ num: this.state.num + 5 });\r\n        }\r\n    }, 5000);\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\ncomponentDidMount() {\r\n    setTimeout(() => {\r\n        for (let i = 0; i < 5; i++) {\r\n            console.log(this.state.num);\r\n            this.setState(prevState => ({ num: prevState.num + 5 }));\r\n        }\r\n    }, 5000);\r\n}\r\n```",
